https://w3id.org/babelon/comment.value: label of HP:0030824 (Mizuo phenomenon)  ; abnormality of the eye

value.value: Change in the color of the fundus from red in the dark-adapted state to golden immediately or shortly after the onset of the light. The color of the fundus reflex in the light adapted state has also been described as golden-yellow, gray-white, and yellow-white. This reflex can appear either homogeneous or in streaks in the fundus. The retinal vessels appear to be protruding in contrast to the radiant background. Dark adaptation leads to disappearance of the unusual fundus coloration [Digital Journal of Ophthalmology 2008; Volume 14, Number 14].

Işığın başlangıcından hemen veya kısa bir süre sonra organ içinin renginin koyu renkle uyarlanmış haldeki kırmızıdan altın renge dönüşmesi. Işığın adapte haldeki fundus refleksinin rengi de altın sarısı, gri-beyaz ve sarı-beyaz olarak tanımlanmıştır. Bu refleks fundusta homojen veya çizgiler şeklinde görülebilir. Retinal damarlar, ışıltılı zeminin aksine çıkıntılı görünmektedir. Karanlık adaptasyon olağandışı fundus renkleşmesinin kaybolmasına yol açar [Digital Journal of Ophthalmology 2008; Cilt 14, Sayı 14]

Zdá se, že retinální cévy vystupují v kontrastu zářivého pozadí. Adaptace na tmu vede k vymizení neobvyklého zbarvení očního pozadí [Digital Journal of Ophthalmology 2008; Svazek 14, číslo 14]

value.value: Crackles are discontinuous, explosive, and nonmusical adventitious lung sounds normally heard in inspiration and sometimes during expiration. Crackles are usually classified as fine and coarse crackles based on their duration, loudness, pitch, timing in the respiratory cycle, and relationship to coughing and changing body position.

Krepitus se obvykle dělí na jemný a hrubý podle délky trvání, hlasitosti, výšky tónu, načasování v dechovém cyklu a vztahu ke kašli a změně polohy těla.

https://w3id.org/babelon/comment.value: label of HP:0030843 (Cardiac amyloidosis)  ; abnormality of metabolism/homeostasis ; abnormality of the cardiovascular system

value.value: 心臓アミロイドーシス

Extracellular deposition in cardiac tissue of a proteinaceous material that, when stained with Congo red, demonstrates apple-green birefringence under polarized light and that has a distinct color when stained with sulfated Alcian blue. Viewed with electron microscopy, the amyloid deposits are seen to be composed of a beta-sheet fibrillar material. These nonbranching fibrils have a diameter of 7.5 to 10 nm and are the result of protein misfolding.

Extracelulární depozice proteinového materiálu v srdeční tkáni, který, když je obarven konžskou červení, vykazuje pod polarizovaným světlem jablkově zelený dvojlom a který má zřetelnou barvu, když je obarven sulfatovanou alciánovou modří. Při pohledu pomocí elektronové mikroskopie je vidět, že amyloidní depozita jsou složena z fibrilárního materiálu beta-listu. Tyto nerozvětvené fibrily mají průměr 7,5 až 10 nm a jsou výsledkem špatného skládání proteinů

value.value: An anomaly of the jugular venous pressure. value.value: Muayene eden kişi, ortalama juguler venöz basıncını gözlemlerken, karaciğere 10 saniye boyunca sert ama devamlı bir basınç uygular. Normalde, juguler venöz basıncında hiç yükselme olmaz ya da sadece geçici (yani, 2 ila 3 saniye) yükselme vardır. Abdominal kompresyon serbest bırakılana kadar ortalama venöz basıncında sürekli bir artış anormaldir ve sağ kalp işlevinde bozulma olduğunu gösterir. Bu anormal yanıt hepatojugular reflü olarak adlandırır

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: The examiner applies firm but persistent pressure over the liver for 10 seconds while observing the mean jugular venous pressure. Normally there is either no rise or only a transient (i.e., 2 to 3 sec) rise in mean jugular venous pressure. A sustained increase in the mean venous pressure until abdominal compression is released is abnormal and indicates impaired right heart function. This abnormal response is called hepatojugular reflux.
